Name: Aston
Description: The Division of Aston consists of Knox City Council.
ProductsAndIndustry: Light industry, including electronics, chemical production, food manufacturing, retail and healthcare services.
NameDerivation: Named in honour of Matilda 'Tilly' Ann Aston, 1873-1947. Aston was a blind writer and teacher who founded the Victorian Association of Braille Writers in 1894 and the Associateion for the Advancement of the Blind. Aston was also the head of the School for the Blind.
DemographicRating: Outer Metropolitan - situated in capital cities and containing large areas of recent suburban expansion.
